Introduction to Java (Simple Explanation)
Java is a programming language used to create software applications. It is widely used because it is easy to learn, secure, and runs on many devices (computers, mobile phones, ATMs, etc.).

Key Points About Java:
High-Level Language ‚Äì Java is written in a way that is easy for humans to understand.
Platform Independent ‚Äì "Write Once, Run Anywhere" (WORA). This means Java code can run on any system without modification.
Object-Oriented ‚Äì Java follows the concept of objects and classes, making programs more structured and reusable.
Secure & Robust ‚Äì Java has built-in security features and strong memory management.
Used Everywhere ‚Äì Java is used for web applications, mobile apps (Android), banking systems, and more.
